	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98353199616675><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Soloing a Shaman lvl 14 to 23</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 2nd 6:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with most of what you say, and I think that the biggest differance is you miss understood what I ment.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>When I said like, I did not mean as good as.  <br><br>I believe I said shaman begin the change from melee to mana, not that they change from mana to melee, if not that is what I ment. <br><br>lvl 19 to 23 are the hardest lvl to solo a shaman.  It became easyer after Kunark.  Because of higher damage weapons that a pre lvl 24 shaman can buy. But at these lvls the shaman's melee skills compaired to the mob he is soloing are at their lowest point, and his/her magic is not yet strong enough to make up the diffrence.  Yes there are some mobs that can be soloed, but when compaired to lvl 24 or lvl 14 your ability to solo is poor.  <br><br>Tipicaly Druids don't have to worry about ac therfor they normaly have more wis items, while the soloing shaman has to maintain his ac.  Therefore tipicaly Druids have a larger mana pool.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
