<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=98354351918745></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98354351918745><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98354351918745>RE: Soloing a Shaman lvl 14 to 23</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98354351918745#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>160 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 2nd 9:31 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmm, I do not think I was disputing you said from melee to mana.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do agree with that assertion.  However, your melee skills can still be your main damage source until much higher than 19, if you &gt;really&lt; want them to be.<br><br>The difficulty of 19 to 23 getting easier isn't because of the new, higher damage weapons.  Lake of Ill Omen, or Overthere at the Warsilik's Woods zoneline will let you &gt;fly&lt; through these levels, at least compared to before.  And yes I agree until 24 life as a solo Shaman sucks =(  You just have to maximize what you have.<br><br>Your whole post was about using Druid/Wizard tactics to solo.  Then you go on to say that we can't do the things they do nearly as well.  On top of that you assert we will have a smaller mana pool. You also mentioned &gt;&gt;untwinked&lt;&lt;.  Well, except for some VERY lowgrade jewel craft items, noone is going to have any + mana or wis items worth mentioning pre level 24.  As I pointed out in my post, 1 wis = 2 mana at level 20.  Unless you have a difference of 50 wisdom, it is not even a single nuke.  And who says you can't wear the same gear as a Druid?  Most of the common, low level +wis/mana gear that is Druid wearable, is Shaman wearable.  Granted, we can't snare kite, but we can root/nuke/DoT.  Ewwww, root/nuke.  Root/DoT is &gt;so&lt; much better =/<br><br>If both are twinked, a Shaman can STILL match the wisdom output of a Druid, AND have a higher AC.  Before I went for more AC, I had a 190+ Wis with my Barbarian Shaman.  Consider that I started out 10 points lower than a Wood Elf or Halfling Druid.... I found that even having all that extra wisdom did not help much.  Having one extra nuke did not make a difference once medded to full. If it did, I was already running for a zoneline.  Mind you, I did quite well before I started getting the bigger Wisdom items *shrug*<br><br>My whole point is:  a)Don't use Druid or Wizard tactics.  Use Shaman tactics. b) Don't believe the hype about wisdom.  Yes, it determines your mana before + mana gear, but it is not a pronounced difference at lower levels.  At level 24, you will need almost 50 extra wisdom to get one more 100 mana nuke or DoT off, and that is from FULL mana.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Drindal <br>43 Monk BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
