	   <tr><td colspan=2>First and formost I agree melee can be a major part of damage well after lvl 19.&nbsp;&nbsp;The point I was trying to make is:  Before lvl 14 a shaman's only real damage comes from melee.  At lvl 14 for the first time a shaman can do real damage with mana.  <br><br>As far as using druid tatics and wiz tatic:  My point is this:  At lvl 14 to lvl 19 we can kill in this way.  Is it the way we should kill for ever more? No.  Is it how I recomend killing at higher lvl? No.  Is there a better way for a shaman to solo? Yes.  Can a lvl 23 shaman solo in the best way for a higher lvl shaman? No.  The point is the strengths of  shaman change with lvl.  If you want to have continuning sucess soloing a shaman you need to embrace the new and from time to time let go of the old.  As I recall at the end of that post i suggested a methood that used both melee and mana.  For lvl 14-23 the killing power of the shaman are Melee and DD.  Dots are starting to play a role, but as of yet the formor two will account for most the damage of a shaman for these lvl.  <br><br>As far as the wisdom of twinked shaman go, I have a good friend with a lvl 9 shaman that has 189 wisdom.  At lvl 20 she recives 316 mana points from her equipment. <br><br>As you well see i agree 100 percent that you should not use druid or wiz tatics to solo your shaman.  I gave 3 examples of how a shaman could solo these lvls.  1 using druid tatics.  2. Using wiz tatics.  3. A combanation of kitting and melee wich was the one I recomended.  <br><br> <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
